headline: Sterling Hits 6.5-Month Low Against Dollar After Weak U.K. PMI Data
summary: Sterling extended losses against the dollar, falling to a six-and-a-half-month low, and pared gains versus the euro after the provisional November U.K. PMI survey came in well below expectations.
